<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-10-26T15:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-10-26T15:00:00-05:00" n="374" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d374">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 658.119/674</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss>
                                    to the Chargé in Great Britain</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LIB1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Laughlin</hi></persName>)</head>
                            <opener>
                                <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                            </opener>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-10-26T16:00:00-04:00">
                                        <hi rend="italic">October 26, 1918, 4 p.m.</hi>
                                    </date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>2440. For <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_SLP1">Sheldon</persName> [from War Trade Board]:</p>
                            <p>No. 1502. Embassy’s 3001, October 22, 6 p.m., your 1723. We concur in
                                the opinion expressed by you in your letter of September 19, No.
                                    5418,<note n="1" xml:id="d374fn1">Not printed.</note> that the
                                total purchase should be considered as a whole and any part taken by
                                any of the Governments or sold be considered <pb facs="0459" n="1293" xml:id="pg_1293"/> for the trio account. In other
                                words, the proceeds of all resales should be pooled and divided
                                equally among the three Associated countries. We assume the resale
                                prices will be submitted for approval to the three Governments. We
                                are now preparing a plan for handling the resales and will submit it
                                to you shortly.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="frus1918Supp01v01#p_LR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>